The paper uses algorithmic game theory to study the placement of UAVs for wireless services, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also focuses on wireless services, which suggests a possible sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of social service cost, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of mechanisms and approximation ratios, which suggests a possible sub-category of control systems (cs.SY) or machine learning (cs.MA).
